      "content": "I hear the exhaustion and the absolute weight you are carrying right now, and it is completely understandable when your mind feels like it has no other options but to keep repeating the same cycle of shame. The feeling of being trapped and unable to move forward with any hope does not fit a simple strategy, so reaching out to a trusted community support line titled with \"National Suicide & Crisis Lifeline\" can provide an immediate place to sit with someone who will listen without judgment or trying to force a fix. Sometimes the only way to stop the noise and feel safe is to let a professional compassionate ear hold the space for you until you feel stable enough to make your own way out of the darkness.",
